From: John Doe <john.doe@somewhere.on.planet>
Date: Sat, 21 Mar 2026 14:47:35 +0000
Subject: ASoC: hdmi-codec: skip startup when monitor is unplugged

When a driver supports HDMI plug detection (hook_plugged_cb) and no
monitor is connected, hdmi_codec_startup() tries to read an all-zero
ELD buffer and logs "HDMI: Unknown ELD version 0" via snd_parse_eld(),
then hw_params and prepare proceed and ultimately fail with -ENODEV
from the platform driver (e.g. dw-hdmi-qp when tmds_char_rate == 0),
producing repeated "ASoC error (-19): at snd_soc_dai_prepare()" spam.

Return -EOPNOTSUPP early when the connector is known to be unplugged.
snd_soc_ret() silences -EOPNOTSUPP, so no error is logged, and the
audio daemon sees a clean "not supported" response rather than a device
error that triggers aggressive retries.

Signed-off-by: John Doe <john.doe@somewhere.on.planet>
---
 sound/soc/codecs/hdmi-codec.c | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/sound/soc/codecs/hdmi-codec.c b/sound/soc/codecs/hdmi-codec.c
index 13ae9e83bc21..a19dce54955e 100644
--- a/sound/soc/codecs/hdmi-codec.c
+++ b/sound/soc/codecs/hdmi-codec.c
@@ -457,10 +457,15 @@ static int hdmi_codec_startup(struct snd_pcm_substream *substream,
 		dev_err(dai->dev, "Only one simultaneous stream supported!\n");
 		mutex_unlock(&hcp->lock);
 		return -EINVAL;
 	}
 
+	if (hcp->hcd.ops->hook_plugged_cb && !hcp->jack_status) {
+		mutex_unlock(&hcp->lock);
+		return -EOPNOTSUPP;
+	}
+
 	if (hcp->hcd.ops->audio_startup) {
 		ret = hcp->hcd.ops->audio_startup(dai->dev->parent, hcp->hcd.data);
 		if (ret)
 			goto err;
 	}
